<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870729-0048 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Avante-Garde Computing Inc.</HL><DD> 07/29/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AVGAEARNINGS (ERN) </IN><TEXT>   Avante-Garde Computing Inc. posted a loss of $4.2 million for its fiscal fourth quarter, ended April 30, compared with a year-earlier deficit of $2.3 million. But the company said it expects to be profitable in its first quarter, ending July 31. For its year-earlier first quarter, the Mount Laurel, N.J.-based maker of management systems for data communications networks posted a loss of $774,000. Revenue in the latest quarter declined 18%, to $3.3 million from $4 million. Separately, the company said that it will begin shipping two new products next month, and that it has obtained a commitment from Midlantic National Bank for a $1 million line of credit to be used for working-capital purposes. </TEXT></DOC>